    "notes": [
      "HSAs require enrollment in a High Deductible Health Plan (HDHP).",
      "Catch-up contribution ($1,000) available for age 55+.",
      "HSA funds roll over indefinitely \u2014 triple tax advantage (deductible, tax-free growth, tax-free qualified withdrawals).",
      "After age 65, non-medical withdrawals taxed as ordinary income (no penalty) \u2014 functions like traditional IRA.",
      "For FEHB: GEHA HDHP and a few other plans are HSA-compatible.",
      "HDHP minimum deductible and OOP maximums shown are IRS requirements for HSA eligibility."
    ]
  },
